[blad 6] The name 'Fluweelen Bruegel' appears in Denucé for the first time in 1653 (Inv. Jer. Wildens), before that time only Jan Bruegel. The name 'Helschen Bruegel' already in Valckenisse Inv. 1614. Fluweelen also in Stevens Inv. 1668; Peter Bruegel in XVII is probably always P.B.II. Ouden Bruegel = P.B.I mostly; 'Breugel' in XVII C. = J.B.I.;
