Bruegel: Months. Importance of the Van Orley Series: Chasses de Maximilien (Tapestries in the same direction as the Louvre drawings the [onleesbaar] cartoons of course in reverse)
For composition:
1) First tapestry (Lugt 178) [= Frits Lugt, Musée du Louvre : inventaire général des dessins des écoles du Nord : maîtres des anciens Pays-Bas nés avant 1550, Paris: Éditions des musées nationaux, 1968, pp. 52-57] (here March) leads into picture frame left to right; 
2) Last one (Lugt 189) Here February leading from right to left (Hommage au Roi Modus et la Reine Ratio); 
3) Rhytmic use of trees; 
4) Trees leading into depth (like in Vienna Hunters in the Snow), though less well organised;
5) Flambée du Sanglier (Lugt 188) in January.

